.TH SRS 1 "March 2026" "srs 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
srs \- Speakly Spaced Repetition System
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B srs
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B srs
is a CLI tool that syncs your learned vocabulary from Speakly and provides
spaced repetition review using the SM\-2 algorithm. Built for local use with
a SQLite database.
.PP
On first sync, you will be prompted to paste a cURL command copied from your
browser's devtools (Network tab). This provides the authentication headers
needed to access the Speakly API. Headers are saved for subsequent syncs and
automatically re\-prompted if the session expires.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B sync
Fetch words from the Speakly API and store them locally. By default, stops
early when a full page contains only already\-known cards. New cards are
immediately available for review.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-full
Fetch all pages without early stopping. Useful to update existing card data
(translations, grammar tips).
.TP
.B \-\-from\-file \fIFILE\fR
Import cards from a JSON file instead of the API. Accepts both a raw results
array and the full API response format with a \fBresults\fR key.
.RE
.TP
.B review
Start an interactive review session. Shows all cards due today (where
\fBnext_review <= today\fR), ordered oldest first.
.RS
.PP
For each card:
.IP 1. 3
The German sentence is shown with hidden words replaced by underscores,
along with the Polish translation hint.
.IP 2. 3
Press \fBEnter\fR to reveal the full sentence, translations, and
per\-word meanings. Audio pronunciation plays automatically.
.IP 3. 3
Rate your recall:
.RS
.TP
.B 1 (Again)
Forgot completely. Card resets and comes back tomorrow.
.TP
.B 2 (Hard)
Recalled with difficulty. Interval advances slowly.
.TP
.B 3 (Good)
Normal recall. Interval follows standard SM\-2 progression.
.TP
.B 4 (Easy)
Instant recall. Interval grows faster.
.RE
.TP
.B r
Replay the pronunciation audio.
.TP
.B q
Quit the session. Progress on already\-rated cards is saved.
.RE
.TP
.B stats
Display learning statistics: total cards, cards due today, cards reviewed
today, never\-reviewed cards, mature cards (interval >= 21 days), and a
7\-day upcoming review forecast.
.TP
.B browse \fR[\fIquery\fR]
Browse or search the word bank. Without a query, lists the first 50 cards
ordered by Speakly position (frequency rank). With a query, searches across
German phrases and Polish translations.
.SH SM\-2 ALGORITHM
The review system uses a standard SM\-2 spaced repetition algorithm.
.PP
.B Interval progression
(when rating Good):
.br
1 day \(-> 6 days \(-> interval \(mu ease_factor \(-> ...
.PP
.B Ease factor
starts at 2.5 and adjusts based on ratings. Minimum is 1.3. Easy ratings
increase the factor; Again/Hard ratings decrease it.
.PP
Cards rated Again are reset to a 1\-day interval regardless of their
previous progress.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.speakly\-srs/srs.db
SQLite database containing all cards and review state.
.TP
.I ~/.speakly\-srs/headers.json
Saved HTTP headers parsed from the cURL command, used for API authentication.
.TP
.I ~/.speakly\-srs/config.json
Optional configuration file. Supported keys:
.RS
.TP
.B language_pair_id
Speakly language pair ID (default: 15, German\-Polish).
.TP
.B daily_review_limit
Maximum cards per review session (default: 100).
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
First\-time sync:
.B srs sync
.br
(Prompts for cURL command from browser devtools)
.TP
Full re\-sync of all cards:
.B srs sync \-\-full
.TP
Import from a JSON file:
.B srs sync \-\-from\-file words.json
.TP
Start a review session:
.B srs review
.TP
Search for a word:
.B srs browse Freund
.TP
View statistics:
.B srs stats
